  "prompt": "Can I write C# on a Mac?",
  "response": "Yes, you can write C# on a Mac. There are several ways to do this:\n\n1. **Visual Studio for Mac**: Microsoft offers a version of Visual Studio specifically designed for macOS. This provides a comprehensive development environment for C# and .NET development.\n\n2. **Visual Studio Code**: This is a lightweight, open-source code editor from Microsoft that supports C# development through extensions. It's available on macOS and can be used with the .NET Core SDK.\n\n3. **JetBrains Rider**: This is a cross-platform .NET IDE developed by JetBrains, which works well on macOS and supports C# development.\n\n4. **Command Line**: You can use the .NET Core SDK on macOS to compile and run C# programs from the terminal.\n\nTo get started, I recommend installing Visual Studio for Mac or Visual Studio Code along with the .NET Core SDK. This will provide you with a robust development environment for writing and running C# code on your Mac.",
